Text.Value: *A calm settles over you. The elder brain is a menace - but you are the Blade of Frontiers. No abomination is too powerful for you to overcome.*
You are no aristocrat. You will be the Blade of Avernus, hunter of fiends and foul beasts.
*You fought to right the wrongs of the Coast, to slay the men and monsters that hunt the helpless.*
*A calm settles over you. The elder brain is a menace - but you are the Blade of Avernus. No abomination is too powerful for you to overcome.*
*Courage. Insight. Strategy. Justice. These were the lessons your father taught you, and the ones by which you will guide your fair city.*
*Even though you bear the horns of a devil, the patriars and people will recognise your claim.*
*It is in the wilds that you find your courage, not in the florid halls of Upper City estates.*
*When the elder brain has fallen, you could even claim your father's own ducal title and carry his banner.*
*You will tread the same halls as your father and command the same marshals.*
*Uncertainty grips you. You have reached a fork in your path. In which direction will you travel?*
*Baldur's Gate is your home, and you are its servant, relentless in your pursuit of the greatest good.*
You are no aristocrat. You are forever the Blade of Frontiers, hunter of foul beasts.
*There will be no great tempest roaring through the skies, no dragon redeemer to help save the city.*
*You should have known. You should always have known.*
You can't be Grand Duke. Mizora would wield too much over Baldur's Gate.

EditorData.logicalname: Still pacted (almost always but not guaranteed)

Text.Value: *For as long as demons and devils imperil the Sword Coast, they will be your prey.*
*There will be no Grand Duke Wyll Ravengard. And there will be no Blade of Frontiers.*
*You are overcome with visions of grand battles and ducal intrigue. Your future looks bright indeed.*
*You are the Blade of Frontiers.*
The power is irresistible. You will be a Grand Duke, and the people will cheer your name.
*No manner of duke should be tied to a devil's leash. No manner of duke should save a city, only to open a gate to the Hells.*
*Your parasite trembles. Even in sleep, your companions know your path, and cry out in victory.*
*You are the warrior who will slay the Absolute. You are the guardian who will defend Baldur's Gate.*
*Your parasite shudders for a moment. Your companions know your path, but none celebrate it.*
The Blade is dead. You will be Wyll Ravengard, proud and just Duke of Baldur's Gate.
*Yet you will labour under Mizora's shadow. What fiendish plans could she be concocting?*
*Your father's memory will fade, and you will be the Ravengard the histories remember.*
*Ansur is dead.*
*To bend the will of the citizens with a single decree, to turn the heads of your adorers and twist the arms of your opponents: affairs of state are your calling.*
*The Blade of Frontiers is dead. You will be Wyll Ravengard, son of Ulder, proud Duke of Baldur's Gate.*
*Baldur's Gate is your home, and you are its servant, relentless in your pursuit of the greatest good. You would sooner die by Mizora's hand than endanger the city.*
*You will make a name for yourself, you will conquer all of the city's ills. The people will know you forever as the Heart of the Gate.*
*You are the Blade of Avernus.*
*Your parasite shudders for a moment. Your companions know your path, but only one celebrates it.*
*When evil's shadow darkened the Sword Coast, you brought your light. You are the people's protector. To fell monsters and guard the meek is your calling.*

Synopsis: Wyll avatar has obtained the Helm of Balduran, and Ravengard is dead. When he sleeps the following night in camp, he contemplates the choice before him. Note that 99% of the time he will be pacted, but he might have killed Ravengard himself.
